Ad Text:
Service Designer

Contract Term
Initial 12 month contract with two possible 12 month extensions

Locations
Canberra, Sydney, Melbourne or Brisbane
Hybrid work model. A minimum of two days per week in the office.

About the Role

An opportunity exists for an experienced Service Designer to join a major digital transformation program within a large federal government environment. The program supports critical national health functions across regulatory and subsidisation lifecycles, while also maintaining ongoing operational support for enterprise platforms including Microsoft Dynamics 365 and the Power Platform.

You will play a key role in bridging business requirements and technical design, collaborating closely with architects, technical leads and multidisciplinary delivery teams. This position is suited to a seasoned systems analyst with deep technical understanding, strong stakeholder engagement skills and the ability to lead investigations and solution design in complex enterprise environments.

Key Responsibilities
Contribute to high level and detailed system designs in collaboration with architects and technical leads
Facilitate technical design workshops and support business clarification where required
Develop and promote reusable enterprise patterns that align system design with business objectives
Work with UX and UI designers and researchers to ensure accessibility and compliance with the Digital Service standards
Translate business needs into clear and actionable system requirements for development teams
Lead root cause investigation and issue resolution for complex production systems
Oversee the transition of project delivered features into Business as Usual support
Produce and maintain high quality system documentation including technical and functional designs, ERDs, data models, schemas and interface specifications
Support Agile delivery activities including sprint planning, backlog refinement and feature breakdown
Conduct peer reviews and contribute to quality assurance processes
Transfer knowledge and uplift capability across the team throughout the engagement
Essential Criteria
Minimum five years recent experience as a Senior Designer or Senior Systems Analyst within a Commonwealth environment
Demonstrated experience working in Agile multidisciplinary teams using Agile methodologies
Strong communication skills with the ability to influence stakeholders to support strategy, delivery decisions and project outcomes
Ability to devise creative and practical solutions to complex problems
Ability to work effectively in fast paced environments and adapt quickly to changing priorities
Demonstrated capability across all functions required of a Senior Systems Analyst
Desirable Criteria
Experience with Dynamics 365 CRM, Power Pages, Dataverse and Azure DevOps
Experience with SQL, Teradata and reporting tools such as Power BI
Exposure to API implementation
Degree level qualification in information technology or a related field

Brunel has partnered with a leading resources company on a contract opportunity for an Data Analyst. Ideal for a data analyst/data scientist with mining and telemetry experience who can turn complex operational data into trusted, actionable insights.

Description

This role delivers data models, analytics, and decision-support tools that improve safety, performance, and operational efficiency of a Collision Avoidance System across mining operations. You'll work across operational, sensor, and spatial datasets to support incident review, optimisation, and strategic decision making, partnering with operations, engineering, and technology teams to define metrics and embed data-driven practices.

Key outcomes:

Analytical models and data pipelines that are robust, accurate, maintainable, and trusted by stakeholders.
Predictive models and statistical analysis using spatial data for creating visualisations, reports and decision making.
Integrated, well-governed datasets combining sensor, geological, and operational data to support repeatable analysis and decision making.
Well-documented business cases and analytical findings that inform product, process, and technology decisions.

Key Responsibilities:

Apply statistical and machine learning techniques to analyse operational and sensor datasets; build predictive models to identify trends and anomalies.
Integrate diverse data sources (sensor, geological, operational) into reliable datasets for analysis and reporting.
Design algorithms that support optimisation and automation, working with developers on proof-of-concepts where needed.
Build dashboards and visualisations that make complex analysis easy to understand, partnering with UI/UX teams as required.
Run stakeholder workshops to gather requirements, identify opportunities, and support adoption of process improvements.
Work with architecture and delivery teams to map analytics impacts to solution requirements.
Partner with IT/data platform teams to ensure data security, integrity, and availability.
Drive continuous improvement by identifying where data can improve safety, productivity, and decision making.

Profile

Bachelor's degree in Computer Science, Statistics, or a related discipline.
Proven experience delivering data analytics/data science in an industrial environment, ideally mining.
Strong programming capability in Python (or Matlab/R).
Experience with geospatial tooling (e.g. ArcGIS or similar).
Experience with modern data platforms (Snowflake and AWS analytics services).
Experience with dashboards/visualisation tools (Power BI, Tableau, Grafana or similar).
Strong communication skills and a structured, detail-focused approach to data quality and documentation.
3+ years' experience in mining operations; knowledge of open pit mining (iron ore preferred).

Highly regarded:

Experience with telemetry and sensor datasets (V2X, heavy mobile equipment, or safety systems).
Familiarity with OT environments, mine control, or autonomy operations.
Experience working with large-scale IoT datasets and networks.
Background supporting safety analysis, incident investigations, or continuous improvement programs with data.
Exposure to production-grade data pipelines and cloud analytics tooling.

Job Offer

We specialise in highly skilled roles across a variety of technical, professional, trades and craft disciplines, pairing candidates with industry-leading projects and organisations on a contract, permanent or secondment basis.

Operating in Australasia since 1997, Brunel has major bases of operation in Perth, Sydney, Brisbane and Port Moresby, which are further backed by the strength and reach of a truly global network spanning over 45 countries, 120 offices and 45 years of successful operation.

Brunel is proud to be equal opportunity employer and encourages applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander and female candidates.

Resume
Cover Letter (optional)

Reporting directly to the CFO and working closely with the most senior stakeholders in the business, this product- focused role will cover budgeting and forecasting, as well as competitor analysis, product analysis and market analysis.

It is a highly commercial and varied role, that would suit a curious and proactive analyst who understands market and competitor dynamics. You will support the product team with new product analysis, decision making around product changes and insights around customer behaviour. 

COMPANY
A lending success story, this ASX listed organisation is on an exciting growth trajectory while still being small enough to enable nimble & quick decisions. With new products launching they are well-funded and have a culture of success & high performance.

Hybrid working - 3 days in office and 2 from home.

Ad Text:
RESERVE BANK OF AUSTRALIA - BANKING DEPARTMENT (RBA BK)

Our business is unique in providing financial services to Commonwealth agencies and overseas central banks. The bank plays an important role in the Australian Payment Board, modernising the Australian Payment Industry. There have been increasing number changes recently, especially with the Australian Payment Network announcing the decommission of the Bulk Electronic Clearing System (BECS). This prompts the opportunity to move to other modern payment system such as New Payment Platform (NPP). RBA BK is a major participant in BECS, sending and receiving welfare, pension, Medicare, child support, tax payments etc.

Role Overview:

We are seeking 2 highly skilled and experienced Senior Business Analysts (x1 Perm role & x1 2-year max-term contract) with deep knowledge of payment processing and ISO 20022 messages. In this pivotal role, you will help lead the analysis and implementation of a crucial Australia's payment system. You will be performing impactful work that helps make a difference to the Australian people.

Key Responsibilities:

Prepare and lead Release Planning activities.

Manage and prioritise backlog with support of Product Owner

Prepare and lead agile ceremonies such as Back log refinement, Sprint Prioritisation and Sprint Planning

Elicit, analyse, and document business requirements.

Participate in solution workshops to ensure quality and fitness for purpose.

Propose/Recommend solutions.

Translate and communicate business, strategic, and technical information to a wide range of stakeholders.

Collaborate with internal and external stakeholders.

Collaborate, be a team player.

Help the team continuously improve to deliver high-quality solutions efficiently.

Provide subject matter expert guidance to assist in other delivery aspects such as implementation planning, change management, test planning and training materials.

Help identify and mitigate risks associated with deliverables.

Help build a high-performance team through knowledge sharing.

Provide guidance to senior Business Analyst.


Qualifications and Experience:

Proven experience as a Business Analyst, preferably within the banking or financial services industry.

Proven experience as a Lead Business Analyst, working with various level experienced Business Analysts

Good knowledge and experience of ISO 20022 standards and their application in financial messaging processes.

Exceptional communication and stakeholder management abilities.

Strong understanding of Agile methodologies and experience working within a scrum team.

Excellent critical thinking and problem-solving skills

Experience with NPP and/or BECS is a plus.


Your Team

We're high-performance team in a fast and dynamic environment.

You will be a member of a delivery team consisting of product owner/delivery manager, scrum master, other Business Analysts, testers and developers in agile development.

You will be reporting to the delivery manager.

You will be working collaboratively within your scrum team and across other scrum teams.

You will be encouraged to speak up and use intelligent inquiry in your everyday work, deliverables, and ways of working.

You will be based at Head Office in Sydney.

We're flexible and operate in hybrid model.

Continuous improvement is our DNA so there will be opportunities for learning and growth.



The Reserve Bank of Australia is committed to equity, diversity and inclusion through key initiatives. We welcome and encourage applicants from diverse backgrounds to apply, including Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples, culturally and linguistically diverse background, those living with a disability and from the LGBTQ+ community. We are committed to making the recruitment process fair and equitable for all our candidates.

What's the role?

We’re looking for a Research Director to help us reinvent how research and insight is done at News Corp Australia. Reporting to the Head of Research, you won't be a traditional Director; rather, you will be someone obsessed with the future of research, technology, and generative AI, finding ways to make insight work faster, smarter, and more impactful. You will be passionate about turning audience insight into decisions that improve products and commercial outcomes, while working on projects that influence the future direction of the country and advocate for a better Australia.

In this role, you will:

Lead Strategic Research: Craft and lead high-impact research programs across diverse topics like media, sport, and the economy. These programs will inform product vision, company priorities, and long-term bets in an AI era.

Modern Execution: Design and conduct quantitative and qualitative research yourself and through external agencies. You'll use modern analytics and AI tools to accelerate analysis while retaining strong human judgement.

Data Synthesis: Triangulate and verify insights by combining multiple data sources primary research, first-party data, and third-party sources to build robust, defensible conclusions.

Commercial Storytelling: Deliver commercially-oriented insights through influential storytelling and strategic foresight to support decision-making across business units.

Team Leadership: Manage a Research Manager and model leadership behaviours that inspire the team, contributing to the development of a best-in-class capability within the Growth Intelligence Centre.

Who are you?

Experience & Background: 8+ years’ experience in market research or insights with an agency background preferred. You are currently functioning as a Research Director or a Senior Manager ready to step up.

Future-Focused Mindset: You aren't a traditional researcher. You are energised by the future of insights and excited to experiment with generative AI tools to automate work and amplify impact.

Technical Expertise: Deep experience designing quantitative or mixed-method studies and conducting market sizing. You have advanced knowledge of Q or SPSS, Excel, and research knowledge platforms.

Analytical Rigour: A demonstrated ability to cross-check and stress-test insights using multiple data sources with high attention to detail and quality standards.

Communication Skills: Excellent presentation and storytelling abilities. You can connect disparate information into clear narratives for senior stakeholders and clients.

Collaborative Drive: A proactive, opportunity-spotting mindset with strong skills in managing stakeholders, cross-functional teams, and supplier relationships.

News Benefits

News Benefits is our way of saying thank you to our people for their valued contribution to News, our audiences, clients and communities. Thanking them for the great things they do daily, for the greater good of Australia. Our benefits include:

Exclusively ours - Access to publications and products from across the News Corp family

Health & wellbeing - Advice, support and facilities for healthy minds and bodies (including an onsite gym at our Adelaide, Brisbane & Sydney offices) 

Time off - News offers a range of leave options to support your personal needs and moments that matter in life: Parental leave, Birthday leave, Volunteer leave, Career break and Compassionate leave.

Helping you grow - Development opportunities (including diversity and inclusion - focused education series) and recognition

Financial wellbeing - Support on making the most of your money

Perks & discounts - Exclusive offers across a range of products and services

Giving back - Make a difference to our communities.

Workplace Inclusion and facilities – Engage with your passions through various employee-resource groups and accessibility to multi-faith quiet rooms & parents’ rooms

Who are we?

We are Australia’s number one and most influential media organisation with more than 150 prestige brands across news, sport and lifestyle. Each month more than 17 million Australians choose to consume news and information from our digital and print products – more than any other media group in Australia.

What’s next?

Apply now or for more information on careers at News Corp Australia visit www.newscorpaustralia.com/careers

Our Commitment to Diversity, Equity and Inclusion We know that diversity strengthens our teams and newsrooms as we seek to tell stories that represent the diverse communities of Australia that we serve. Our people make us unique and we all have a story. We encourage people of all ages, backgrounds, races, cultures, religions, sexual orientations, abilities and gender identities to apply. Inclusion is important to us and we want everyone at News to bring their whole-selves to work. If you require any accommodations or adjustments throughout the recruitment process, or would like to outline which pronouns you prefer, please feel free to let us know.

We are seeking an experienced Change Analyst to provide hands-on delivery, analytical and coordination support to a Program Change Manager on an ICT Modernisation program of work.

The role will focus on supporting the execution of a variety of change management activities and coordinating stakeholder engagement activities and inputs. It will also involve developing and maintaining change artefacts, processes and registers, as well as producing clear insights to enable effective program change management, informed decision-making, and successful adoption outcomes.

You will have demonstrated experience supporting organisational change, ideally within an ICT initiative. They will have a sound understanding of change management approaches and principles, and strong analytical and communications skills.

This role requires you to work in the Canberra office at least 3 days per week.

Duties and responsibilities include, but are not limited to, the following:

Maintain and manage program-level change registers, including stakeholder, change impact and engagement registers, to support a coordinated view of change across the program
Develop, maintain and continuously improve change management processes, templates and tools to ensure consistent application across the program
Provide analytical support to the Program Change Manager, including consolidation of change inputs, identification of cross-project impacts and dependencies, and change and engagement saturation
Support program-level reporting and governance activities by preparing dashboards, status updates and briefing inputs for forums and decision-makers
Assist with the development of change-related communications materials in collaboration with communications and project teams
Coordinate inputs from project change managers to enable consistent, timely and accurate program-level reporting
Provide general delivery and coordination support to the Program Change Manager to enable efficient, aligned and high-quality change outcomes
Essential Criteria:

Demonstrated experience supporting organisational change activities, ideally within an ICT or transformation initiative
Strong analytical skills with the ability to synthesise information and identify key change impacts, risks and themes
Excellent written and verbal communication skills, with experience preparing clear concise change artefacts, presentations, training and support material, and reports
Strong organisational skills with the ability to manage multiple tasks and priorities in a fast-paced environment
Ability to work collaboratively as part of a team while taking ownership of allocated tasks
Desirable Criteria:

Change management certification
Experience using PowerBI
You MUST be an Australian Citizen and hold a minimum of an NV1 Security Clearance to be considered for this position.

Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted for this role.

For more information contact Mitchell on 0425 269 780

Job description:



About us

We create thriving places and connected communities. We bring together transport, planning, land use, precinct and policy functions in a single department to deliver the best outcomes for Victorians.

Together with our portfolio agencies, we are responsible for planning, building, operating and +maintaining Victoria's transport, planning and land services for use by all.

We foster a safe, inclusive and constructive place to work.

Investment and Technology leads and manages the investment lifecycle; drives commercial advice & negotiations to facilitate reform; and enables core delivery through Finance, Procurement & Technology.

About the role

The Resource and Capability Manager is a key leadership role within the Data & Digital division, responsible for managing a team of project managers and business analysts within the Delivery Branch. This role leads a team of skilled professionals responsible for the successful delivery of Data & Digital projects, meeting organisational objectives and tailored to evolving stakeholder needs.

Key Selection Criteria

The key selection criteria emphasise strong leadership in people management, project delivery and workforce capability development. The role requires the ability to translate organisational strategies into programs and workforce plans, drive performance, champion continuous improvement, and build a culture that enables others to excel. Advanced business analysis skills are also essential, with the capability to apply analytical frameworks in complex settings and contribute to organisational capability uplift.

To access the Position Description, Please click here

Position accountabilities

DTP is seeking an experienced leader to uplift project delivery capability across its Data & Digital division. This role provides assurance and oversight of project and business analysis practices, ensuring compliance with standards, methodologies, and governance requirements. A key focus will be fostering a high-performance culture that promotes collaboration, continuous improvement, and rigorous project disciplines to support successful delivery outcomes.

The position will lead resource planning and optimisation activities, aligning workforce capabilities with project objectives, timelines, and budgets. This includes developing fit-for-purpose resource plans, capacity planning, and development pathways that enhance team performance and adaptability. The role will also champion continuous improvement across project practices and support change initiatives that uplift systems, processes, and portfolio outcomes.Success requires strong analytical and strategic thinking skills, the ability to identify improvement opportunities, and the capacity to influence stakeholders across technical and executive domains. Applicants will bring expertise in risk management, professional development, and cross-functional collaboration, with the confidence to ensure issues are proactively identified and addressed. This is an opportunity to support meaningful transformation and strengthen delivery capability for one of Victoria's most impactful public sector portfolios.

Qualifications and experience

• Tertiary qualifications in IT Systems or related area. (mandatory)

• Experience relevant to the accountabilities and capabilities of the role. (mandatory)

• Formal qualifications in Business and /or Systems Analysis (e.g. CCBA). (desirable)

• Certified Business Analysis Professional (CBAP) (desirable)

• PRINCE II, ITIL 4, Agile certifications (desirable)

• Experience in technology, data and digital delivery. (desirable)

Culture Value

We welcome applicants from a diverse range of backgrounds representing the community that we serve, including veterans, parents, carers, First Peoples, people with disability, multicultural, multifaith and LGBTIQA+ individuals.

As an equal opportunity employer, we are committed to fostering a safe, inclusive, and high-performance culture. Through shared actions and behaviours aligned with our strategy and direction, we empower our people to thrive and meaningfully contribute to the department's goals.

What we offer

Working at the Department of Transport and Planning provides people with the opportunity to contribute to creating thriving places and connected communities for all Victorians.

For further details please refer to Careers at the Department of Transport and Planning.

Pre-employment checks and employment conditions

Applicants must be an Australian Citizen, Permanent Resident or hold a valid work permit or visa necessary for the nature of the position.

Recipients of Victorian Public Service (VPS) voluntary departure packages should note that re-employment restrictions apply.

How to apply

Click the ‘Apply' button to be redirected to our recruitment platform, where you may need to create an account to submit your application.

Applications close at 11.59pm on Wednesday, 25th of February 2025.

If you encounter any issues, refer to our Quick Reference Guide for step-by-step instructions.

Please include both your resume and a cover letter. All applications must be submitted via the online portal, we're unable to accept email or manual submissions.

For further information about the role, please contact Courtenay Oliver, Director, Data and Digital Delivery at Courtenay.oliver@transport.vic.gov.au.

Important Information:

If you require any adjustments to fully participate in the recruitment process, or need the advert or attachments in an accessible format (e.g., large print), please contact us by phone or email. We're here to support you.

Data Governance Advisor

6 Month Contract | $1,200 - $1,350 + Super / Day | Sydney (Hybrid)

We are partnering with a leading Australian university undertaking a significant enterprise Data Governance uplift aligned to a broader digital and data transformation program.

This is a hands-on, embedded role working directly with the Enterprise Data Governance Lead to operationalise governance across priority domains including Student and HR data.

This is not a policy writing or purely advisory engagement. We are seeking a practitioner who has implemented governance in complex, federated organisations and can operate confidently between strategy and execution.

The Opportunity

You will play a key role in translating enterprise data governance intent into practical, adoptable standards and artefacts that can be embedded into delivery and business-as-usual rhythms.

Key focus areas include:

Designing and operationalising minimum viable governance standards.
Defining stewardship models, decision-rights and accountability structures.
Establishing data classification, sensitivity and usage controls.
Contributing to AI and advanced analytics governance requirements.
Supporting governance forums and assurance mechanisms.
Developing practical templates, artefacts and “how-to” guidance.
Facilitating workshops and enabling adoption across faculties and portfolios.
Mentoring internal team members to build sustainable governance capability.
You will work closely with data platform, reporting and domain delivery teams to ensure governance is integrated, not bolted on.

About You

You are a proven Data Governance practitioner who has:

Implemented (not just designed) enterprise data governance frameworks.
Produced governance artefacts that were adopted in practice.
Worked in complex, federated environments (higher education or public sector highly regarded).
Balanced rigour with pragmatism and organisational readiness.
Operated comfortably across senior stakeholders.
Strong influencing, facilitation and mentoring capability.
Experience supporting AI governance or enterprise data platform programs will be highly regarded.

What’s on Offer

6 month contract with strong likelihood of extension
$1,200 - $1,350 + super / day (depending on experience)
Hybrid working - 3 days onsite in Sydney, 2 days WFH
High-impact role within a major institutional transformation
This is an opportunity to contribute meaningfully to an enterprise-wide uplift that will underpin analytics, regulatory obligations and future AI capability at scale.

If you’re a hands-on governance leader who thrives in complex environments and enjoys building capability as you deliver, we’d welcome a confidential discussion.

Job Title: Manager Analytics, Crime and Corruption Commission
Ad Text:
The Crime and Corruption Commission (CCC) is a statutory body set up to combat and reduce the incidence of major crime and corruption in the public sector in Queensland. Its functions and powers are set out in the Crime and Corruption Act 2001.

About us

We have a vision that our communities will be safe and supported by fair and ethical public institutions with a focus on those matters of highest threat to the Queensland community. As an organisation we are committed to this vision and as such our values of people, accountability, integrity, courage and excellence underpin everything we do at the CCC.

• flexible work options, including working from home

How to apply

Company description:



ANALYST FINANCE BUSINESS PARTNERSHIP



Job description:



DISCOVER A BRIGHTER FUTURE

At South32, we're meeting the challenge of enabling a sustainable future through our focus on responsibly producing commodities critical for a low-carbon world. As a collaborative, caring and inclusive company, there's no better place to make a genuine difference. Together we're making a positive, global impact that has the potential to change lives. Whatever career path you choose, we'll support you every step of the way to learn, grow and succeed. So join us, step towards a brighter future and leave your legacy.


ABOUT WORSLEY

Are you looking to be home every night? If so, this is your opportunity to live, work and play a short drive from stunning coastlines, scenic trails, magnificent jarrah forests and the food and wine heartland of the South-West and Peel Regions of Western Australia.

Our integrated Bauxite Mine, Alumina Refinery and Port Operation is creating the essential products needed for a sustainable low carbon future and is on a journey to become the world's leading Alumina producer where our workforce value the lifestyle that Worsley Alumina has to offer.

WHAT SOUTH32 OFFERS

26 weeks full-paid, or 52 weeks half-paid parental leave for primary carers.
Annual short-term incentive bonus that recognises both your individual performance and the overall success of the business.
Discounted rates on travel, healthcare, and technology products.

Ability to purchase up to 4 weeks of additional annual leave.

ABOUT THE ROLE

This is a Permanent, Monday to Friday, 40-hour per week roster. This role will be based at our Worsley Alumina Refinery which is a short drive from Collie (15 minutes), Bunbury (35 minutes) and other nearby scenic communities.

As there is no accommodation on site, you will be required to drive in, drive out on a daily basis. Employees ideally live within an hour's drive of Collie.

As the Analyst Finance Business Partnership, you will be responsible for providing expert financial analysis and advice to support operations in achieving optimal business outcomes.

Key responsibilities include, but are not limited to:

Partnering with operational leaders during budgeting and monthly forecasting cycles
Interpreting cost drivers and clearly explaining impacts on performance and outcomes
Supporting contract set‑up and variations with clear financial input
Strengthening site adherence to financial governance, standards and procedures
Working closely with operational teams to resolve finance‑related issues
Contributing to continuous improvement through data‑led insights and practical recommendations

ABOUT YOU

You will have experience and demonstrate capability in the following:

Working in a finance business partnering or management reporting environment
Building effective, trusted relationships with operational and senior stakeholders
Translating complex information into clear, practical insights for non‑finance audiences
Managing multiple priorities with confidence, curiosity and a collaborative approach
Proficiency in finance software, including SAP & Excel (Power BI advantageous)

Qualifications for this position are:

CA/CPA with relevant Finance Experience

Relocation may be considered for the successful candidate.

South32 is committed to building and maintaining an inclusive and diverse workforce that reflects the communities in which we operate. We provide a recruitment process that is fair, equitable and accessible for all and we encourage candidates from all backgrounds to apply.

The job advert will close on Friday 27 February 2026

We are seeking a Contract Senior Data Architect / Data Modeller to lead the design of a common enterprise data model supporting the migration of fragmented data assets from SAS NEO to a Databricks Lakehouse platform.

This role plays a critical part in establishing a unified, governed data foundation that standardises core entities, definitions, and relationships across the organisation, enabling scalable analytics, reporting, and AI/ML use cases.

You will work across architecture, data engineering, analytics, and business teams to rationalise existing schemas, translate embedded business logic, and define canonical domains aligned to modern Lakehouse and cloud data architecture principles.

Key Responsibilities
Design conceptual, logical, and physical data models supporting enterprise analytics and AI
Define canonical data domains, entities, and relationships
Map legacy SAS NEO datasets and unstructured sources to target Databricks models
Translate embedded business logic into governed, reusable data structures
Define OLTP, OLAP, and dimensional models (star/snowflake)
Establish metadata, lineage, and documentation standards
Ensure alignment with Lakehouse, ELT, and cloud architecture patterns
Collaborate with engineers, architects, and stakeholders on target-state design
Required Skills & Experience
Strong experience in Data Architecture, Data Modelling & Design

Ad Text:
About Us

Join us at Cleanaway and contribute to making a sustainable future possible, together.

We transform waste into resources and renewable energy.  When you start to think of waste as a resource, it opens a world of possibilities.

As a high growth, ASX listed organisation with over 10,000 employees, our goal is to be recognised by our customers as the most innovative and sustainable waste management company with industry leading HSE performance.  We are Australia’s largest company in this sector, providing essential services to millions of customers and communities nationally.

The Opportunity

We are seeking a highly capable and commercially minded Senior FP&A Analyst to join Cleanaway’s Group Finance team on a 6-month fixed-term contract. 

Sitting within the Group FP&A function, this role plays an integral part in delivering Cleanaway’s financial planning and reporting processes, including forecast and monthly reporting. You’ll be responsible for preparing analysis, interpreting financial performance, and providing insights that support decision-making across Group and Corporate stakeholders. Further, you’ll be leading the KPI and Value Driver reporting process, including governance on metrics and reporting. 

This is a hands-on role that would suit an experienced analyst who enjoys the structure of ASX and BAU cycles, has excellent attention to detail, and is confident working with financial systems and large data sets. You will work closely with other analysts, Corporate Finance, and business partners across the Strategic Business Units (SBUs). 

 

Key Responsibilities 

Support the forecasting and budgeting process, working with finance business partners to consolidate, review, and validate inputs. 
Supporting and developing our Key Performance Indicators and Value Drivers across our segments, including the reporting and governance framework. 
Prepare and deliver accurate and timely monthly performance reporting, including actuals vs budget/forecast analysis for both Group, Segment and Corporate Functions. 
Assist with preparation of reporting packs and presentations for Monthly Operating Reviews (MORs) and internal executive stakeholders. 
Work with Corporate Functions to track and report overhead performance, highlighting key drivers and variances. 
Driving the preparation of board reporting, including Board Insight Papers, along with ASX-related external reporting requirements. 
Collaborating with each Strategic Business Units (SBU) to support and align on performance and analysis requirements. 
Use tools such as TM1 (PAW/PAFE) and Power BI to extract, analyse and present data in a clear and meaningful way. 
Assist in the development and maintenance of financial models, templates, and standardised reports. 
Collaborate with the wider Group FP&A team and SBUs to ensure alignment and clarity across financial deliverables and deadlines. 

About You

You bring strong commercial acumen, advanced analytical capability, and the confidence to influence senior stakeholders in a complex organisation.

 

8+ years of experience in Financial Planning & Analysis, management reporting, or similar commercial finance roles. 
Proven experience supporting BAU financial cycles including budgeting, forecasting, and month-end reporting. 
Strong analytical skills with attention to detail, and ability to interpret financial data into clear insights. 
Proficiency in financial systems such as TM1 (PAW/PAFE), Power BI, and advanced Excel. 
Experience working in a large, complex, or matrixed organisation – ASX-listed or similar preferred. 
Strong financial acumen, with an understanding of forecasting methodologies and value drivers. 
Strong interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to work effectively with finance and non-finance stakeholders. 

Why join Cleanaway? 

Competitive salary package
Flexible working arrangements
Career opportunities in a high growth, Australian business
Supportive and safe work environment
Paid parental leave
Great company benefits: Employee share program, company discounts, salary packaging, flu vaccinations, EAP, discounts on private health insurance and more.

We are dedicated to improving employment outcomes and encourage applications from Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander peoples. We also welcome candidates of all ages, abilities, gender identities, experiences (including veterans), and cultural backgrounds.

If you love digging into business processes, running cross-functional projects, driving change, and finding opportunities to streamline and simplify — this role is made for you.

What you’ll do (responsibilities)

Lead Finance Process Transformation: Identify, design, and deliver scalable improvements across key global finance processes (Revenue, Billing, Payables, Reporting, etc.), balancing innovation with strong control and compliance. Help embed AI-enabled ways of working, drive adoption and education, help teams identify problems and expected outcomes - focusing on efficiency, accuracy, repeatability, and standardisation.
Project, Program and Change Management: Lead transformation programs of varying scale, ensuring cross-functional stakeholder alignment, governance, and smooth change adoption across teams. Coordinate project activities, dependencies, and timelines to ensure alignment between teams.Help unblock, remove ambiguity, and support smooth project execution.
Drive Technology Enablement: Partner with Finance Systems, Data, and Engineering teams to implement automation, system integrations, and AI-based solutions that streamline end-to-end workflows.
Help shape the Transformation Roadmap: Collaborating with finance and business leaders to define the strategic direction for the Finance Technology stack and transformation priorities.
Data, Insight & Automation: Champion data-driven decision-making - ensuring finance data is leveraged effectively for reporting, analytics, and automation.

What we're looking for

Significant experience in Finance Transformation, or Process Improvement roles (experience in fast-scaling tech, SaaS, or global environments strongly preferred).
A background in Finance with a Bachelor's degree in Finance, Accounting, Business Administration, or a related field is a big plus.
Experience with driving process redesign. Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, able to break down ambiguity into actionable steps.
Familiarity with finance ERP, billing and reporting systems (e.g., Workday, Netsuite, Zuora, Salesforce, Anaplan) and an understanding of data and automation and AI platforms.
Proven ability to lead large scale transformation programs end-to-end from strategy and design to implementation and embedding.
A balance of big-picture vision and detail orientation, with a strong understanding of finance processes and data flows.
Excellent stakeholder management and communication skills; able to work cross-functionally without effort, translating between finance, technical and business teams.
Growth mindset. Passion for continuous improvement and leveraging new technologies (AI, automation, analytics) to elevate finance impact and scale finance operations.

We'd love it if you have:

Familiarity with Agile, Lean, or continuous improvement approaches.

We’re a small new team that is just getting started, so you aren’t afraid to roll up your sleeves, get into the detail. Able to determine and play whatever role is needed to make projects a success: analyst, project coordinator, facilitator, tester, or change champion.

Why You’ll Love It Here

You’ll shape the future of how finance operates at one of the world’s most loved design platforms.

You’ll work with world-class teams across Finance, IT, Data and the business in an environment that encourages experimentation and learning.

You’ll have autonomy and ownership to lead high-impact transformation initiatives that directly influence Canva’s scalability and success.

What's in it for you?

Achieving our crazy big goals motivates us to work hard - and we do - but you'll experience lots of moments of magic, connectivity and fun woven throughout life at Canva, too. We also offer a range of benefits to set you up for every success in and outside of work.

Here's a taste of what's on offer:

Equity packages - we want our success to be yours too
Inclusive parental leave policy that supports all parents & carers
An annual Vibe & Thrive allowance to support your wellbeing, social connection, office setup & more
Flexible leave options that empower you to be a force for good, take time to recharge and supports you personally

Check out lifeatcanva.com for more info.

Other stuff to know

We make hiring decisions based on your experience, skills and passion, as well as how you can enhance Canva and our culture. When you apply, please tell us the pronouns you use and any reasonable adjustments you may need during the interview process.

We celebrate all types of skills and backgrounds at Canva so even if you don’t feel like your skills quite match what’s listed above - we still want to hear from you!

Please note that interviews are conducted virtually.

Ready to make an impact?

If you’re excited about working with cutting‑edge AI, partnering with global leaders, and joining a high‑growth company, we’d love to hear from you.

For a quicker response, we encourage you to apply directly through our website at https://www.futuresecure.ai/. There, you can meet our Digital Co-worker and experience our product first hand.

Hybrid working, supportive culture, WFH flexibility
$140-160K + super + bonus on offer
